{"questionId":"5175","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Graphing is an important tool in the study of rates of chemical reactions.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Formulate the equation for the reaction of one of the acids produced in (e)(i) with&nbsp;calcium carbonate.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>2HNO<sub>2</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) → Ca(NO<sub>2</sub>)<sub>2</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;CO<sub>2</sub>(g) +&nbsp;H<sub>2</sub>O(l)</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>2HNO<sub>3</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;CaCO<sub>3</sub>(s) → Ca(NO<sub>3</sub>)<sub>2</sub>(aq) +&nbsp;CO<sub>2</sub>(g) +&nbsp;H<sub>2</sub>O(l)</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5175","referenceCode":"18M.2.hl.TZ2.2e.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Formulate the equation for the reaction of one of the acids produced in (e)(i) with calcium carbonate.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"e.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases","8.5 Acid deposition","Core","Topic 8: Acids and bases"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}